{"metadata":{"title":"set(gracefulDisconnect:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"gracefulDisconnect"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:3GIO21TcpConnectionProtocolPAAE3set18gracefulDisconnectySb_tF","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionProtocol"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"gracefulDisconnect","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A graceful disconnect means that we can be sure that we successfully sent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"all the outstanding data to the other end, or get an error reported."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"However, it also means we have to wait for all the data to reach the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other side and for it to acknowledge this by closing the socket, which may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"take a while. For this reason it is disabled by default.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TcpConnectionProtocol\/set(gracefulDisconnect:)"},"kin